@startuml architecture-write-api

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName monospaced
skinparam nodesep 50
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam padding 6

title Write paths to the primary

actor "App without\nDB access" as appA
actor "App with\nDB access" as appB
actor "Co-located app\n(same database)" as appC

note as N1
  **A: pgauthzd-fronted write API**
  pgauthzd verifies the JWT and — via its OPA
  sidecar — the writer role (WRITER_ROLE in
  JWT_ROLES_CLAIM), records the subject as the
  audit author, then applies the write natively.
  Only pgauthzd calls OPA. (Write-authz
  delegation is the pending pgauthzd-fronted-
  writes increment; today write.rego fronts it.)

  Multi-app: a per-app DB role from a JWT claim
  (DB_ROLE_CLAIM) → pgauthzd SET LOCAL ROLEs to
  it, so **namespace isolation** applies per app.
end note

node "HTTP Write API" as optA {
    component "pgauthzd (writer)\n(full profile)" as pgd #Salmon
    component "OPA\n(sidecar)" as opa #LightBlue
}

database "PostgreSQL\nprimary" as pg #Orange

N1 -right-> pgd

appA -down-> pgd : "A: POST /pgauthz/v1/write\n(JWT: writer role)"
pgd -right-> opa : "authorize write\n(writer-role policy)"
opa -left-> pgd : "authorized"
pgd -down-> pg : "SQL (pgx; authz_writer\nor per-app role)"

appB -down-> pg : "B: direct SQL\nwrite_tuple() /\nwrite_tuples_checked()\n(authz_writer role)"

appC -down-> pg : "C: co-located\nbusiness write + write_tuple()\nin ONE transaction"

note bottom of pg
  All three paths land in the same function API
  (SECURITY DEFINER; app roles never get table
  grants) and the same immutable audit trail.
  C additionally makes the grant **atomic** with
  the business change — see the co-located
  topology. Apps whose tuples derive from their
  own DB rows typically feed A or B via a
  **transactional outbox** (MODEL_DESIGN §10).
end note

legend bottom left
  |= Color |= Component |
  | <#Salmon> | pgauthzd (writer) — full profile; the write front door; consults OPA for authz, applies the write natively |
  | <#LightBlue> | OPA — internal writer-role policy; ONLY pgauthzd calls it |
  | <#Orange> | PostgreSQL — authz schema |
end legend

@enduml
